        <type>void</type>
        <definition>virtual void helios::input::InputAdapter::updateGamepadState</definition>
        <argsstring>(unsigned int gamepadMask) noexcept=0</argsstring>
        <name>updateGamepadState</name>
        <qualifiedname>helios::input::InputAdapter::updateGamepadState</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type>unsigned int</type>
          <declname>gamepadMask</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Updates the <ref refid="classhelios_1_1input_1_1GamepadState" kindref="compound">GamepadState</ref> objects with the values queried from the underlying Gamepad identified by the specified mask. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Updates the <ref refid="classhelios_1_1input_1_1GamepadState" kindref="compound">GamepadState</ref> objects with the current values of the underlying hardware. If querying the underlying hardware fails, this method will update the <ref refid="classhelios_1_1input_1_1GamepadState" kindref="compound">GamepadState</ref> values to a valid initial state (no movement or interaction). Implementations should use `isConnected()` to check whether the current values of a `GamepadState` object can be trusted.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>gamepadMask</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>A bitmask representing all <ref refid="classhelios_1_1input_1_1GamepadState" kindref="compound">GamepadState</ref> objects to update, e.g. Gamepad::ONE | Gamepad::TWO... </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
